description:
Global Banking and Markets – Global Markets

Hang Seng's Global Markets business provides superior service, fully integrated solutions and 24-hour global markets coverage. Our support framework is substantial. Our advanced technologies deliver quick access to key markets. Our capital strength allows us to tailor competitively-priced solutions for specific client business around the world. We provide a full spectrum of treasury services to our customers, including foreign exchange, interest rate risk management, derivatives products, capital markets instruments, as well as market intelligence on global trends and key developments.

We are currently seeking a high caliber professional to join our department as Senior Treasury Solution Dealer II.
  

Principal responsibilities

Serve and provide treasury solutions / products to the Bank’s client with focus on corporate clients;
Indentify sales opportunities or initiatives that address clients’ need;
Maintain business relationships with clients in assigned area of responsibility;
Support the Head of Treasury Solution on business initiatives;
Collaborate with internal stakeholders, including Relationship Managers and other product groups to maximise cross-selling opportunities for the Bank;
Dealing of treasury vanilla products and structure derivatives
Requirements
University degree holder;
Minimum of five years’ working experience as treasury sales with strong connection of corporate clients;
Strong treasury product knowledge especially in FX and interest rate derivatives;
Strong communication and interpersonal skills;
Creative, with growth mindset and highly adaptable to changes and transformation;
Proficiency in both English and Chinese, fluency in Putonghua an advantage;
High level of customer centricity mindset with dedication to deliver exceptional quality services for customers

If you would like to explore other opportunities at Hang Seng Hong Kong, please visit www.hangseng.com/careers/ for details.

The health and safety of our employees and candidates is very important to us. Due to the current situation related to the Novel Coronavirus (2019-nCoV), we’re leveraging our digital capabilities to ensure we can continue to recruit top talent at the HSBC Group.  As your application progresses, you may be asked to use one of our digital tools to help you through your recruitment journey.  If so, one of our Resourcing colleagues will explain how our video-interviewing technology will be used throughout the recruitment process and will be on hand to answer any questions you might have. 

All information provided by applicants will be used only for recruitment purposes and will be used strictly in accordance with the Bank's personal data policies, a copy of which may be obtained by the applicant upon request. Unless otherwise instructed in writing by the applicant concerned, applicants may be considered for other suitable positions within the Bank and its related companies. The personal data of unsuccessful job applicants may be retained for a maximum of two years from the date when the job application is rejected and such data may be retained for a longer period if there is a subsisting reason that obliges the Bank to do so, after which the personal data will be destroyed.

Job Descriptions:
To support treasury operations and settlements for all treasury activities, including documentation review and payment execution;
To perform daily account and position reconciliation;
To support loan administration duties and monitor the performance of appointed loan servicers and agents;
To conduct financial calculation and data analysis with MS Excel and Access;
To provide documents management services;
To participate in ad hoc duties or projects; and
The employment will be on contract basis subject to renewal.
Requirements:


Bachelor degree in Finance, Accounting, Business Administration or related discipline, preferably with 1 year of working experience in commercial banks or financial institutions;
Attention to details, high degree of accuracy, able to work independently, under pressure and meet tight deadlines;
Self-motivated, proactive working attitude, eager to learn and willing to take up new responsibilities;
Excellent command of written and spoken English and Chinese;
Proficient in computer operation including MS Word and MS Excel, knowledge in MS Access an added advantage; and
Fresh graduates will also be considered.
Interested parties please send your full resume stating current and expected salary by 26 January 2022.
Please visit http://www.hkmc.com.hk/eng/careers/job_openings.html for other application methods.
Please ensure that all information provided to the HKMC Group is accurate, complete and updated. Data provided which is inaccurate or incomplete may influence the process and outcome of the recruitment exercise.  Please read the HKMC Group Personal Information Collection Statement for Job Applicants at the HKMC website before completing the application form.  Personal data collected will be used for recruitment purposes only.  Candidates not invited for interview within 8 weeks may consider their application unsuccessful.

To handle the control and reporting function of a bank’s treasury function,including profit attribution analysis, MTM reporting and analysis. Conduct price verification on financial products. Responsible for the assessment of the valuation adjustment, off-market rate checking. Maintain internal control standards on valuation, front to back position break reconciliation etc. Understanding of product control and able to adapt to different bank's policy, procedures quickly. Setup of new controls framework and implementation either due to regulatory changes or new business.Provide advice on control implication on their new business / new product. Participate discussions on Change initiatives, articulate the user requirements, provide input and solutions to new deals/products/initiatives.Participate in system implementation and various projects on financial products .

 Requirements:

Degree holder in Risk Management, Statistic, Economics, Finance, Quantitative Analysis or relevant disciplines, with professional qualifications of CFA, FRM, CPA or equivalent is preferred;
 At least 5 years’ product control market risk management experiences;
Strong knowledge in treasury / global markets products, such as FX products, Fixed Income, Derivatives & OTC products and financial product analytical skill is preferred;
Familiar with trading front & back office systems;
Proficient in MS Excel and practical skill in VBA & SQL;
Strong communication and analytical skills;
Proficient in both spoken and written English and Chinese, fluent in Putonghua is preferable.

If you are flexible enough and zeal for a harmonious and supportive working environment where enables you to grow and succeed professionally, please send a full resume indicating your public examination results (HKCEE and HKALE / HKDSE), your present and expected salary and quoting reference number attention to Talent Acquisition Division, Nanyang Commercial Bank, 151 Des Voeux Road Central,  Hong Kong or apply through email. For details, please visit https://www.ncb.com.hkhttps//www.ncb.com.hk/ and select the page Recruit.

We are an Equal Opportunities Employer. Data collected would be used for recruitment purposes only. Applicants who do not hear from us within 8 weeks may consider their applications unsuccessful and their data will be destroyed within 12 months of receipt.

Formulate strategic business plans and participate in new product development. Maintain clients' relationship and develop marketing plans. Provide market information and trading strategies to clients. Promote treasury products to clients and execute clients’ order. Achieve sales target allocated by management.

Requirements

With Bachelor Degree or above, preferably with major in Finance, Economics, Accounting, business Administration or related disciplines;
At least 5 years working experience in Banking industry, of which at least 3 years working experience in handling treasury products or wealth management products;
Professional qualifications in CFA, FRM and equivalent will be an advantage;
Licensed to dealing in securities (Type 1) and advising on securities (Type 4) is a must;
Familiar with treasury systems e.g Reuters, Bloomberg, Kondor+;
Good presentation, negotiation and analytical skills; Excellent communication and interpersonal skills;
High proficiency in professional computer applications;
Proficient in both spoken and written English and Chinese, fluent in Putonghua is preferable.

(Candidate with less experience will be considered as Assistant Treasury Marketing Manager.)

If you are flexible enough and zeal for a harmonious and supportive working environment where enables you to grow and succeed professionally, please send a full resume indicating your public examination results (HKCEE and HKALE / HKDSE), your present and expected salary and quoting reference number attention to Talent Acquisition Division, Nanyang Commercial Bank, 151 Des Voeux Road Central, Hong Kong or apply through email. For details, please visit https://www.ncb.com.hk/ and select the page Recruit.

We are an Equal Opportunities Employer. Data collected would be used for recruitment purposes only. Applicants who do not hear from us within 8 weeks may consider their applications unsuccessful and their data will be destroyed within 12 months of receipt.

职责
1.监督和处理日常会计，预算和财务相关业务;
2、处理所有与业务相关的交易交易，并备案所有相关记录;
3. 与银行、税务局、公司等相关方维护和实施财务、税务等相关事宜，确保符合会计准则和法定披露要求;
4、准备本地及海外合并、管理报告、预算、预测;
5. 处理临时项目，支持管理层决策。
要求：
1、财务、会计或相关专业本科及以上学历;
2、具有会计资格或完成专业会计机构职业考试的人员，应予考虑;
3、3年以上金融行业工作经验，有贸易公司/投资银行工作经验者优先;
4. 扎实的证券会计、证监会财务资源规则及/或财务申报表经验;
5、有责任心、吃苦耐劳、具有良好的团队合作精神，具有高度的个人诚信;
6. 良好的普通话和英语口语和书面表达能力
注意：通过自愿提交收集的简历将在职位发布后一个月内销毁。

The Treasury Markets Association (TMA) was incorporated through the institutionalisation of the Treasury Markets Forum of Hong Kong and the merger with ACI-The Financial Markets Association of Hong Kong in 2005. Principal functions of the TMA include promoting co-operation and synergy among market practitioners with a view to enhancing professionalism and the overall competitiveness of the treasury markets in Hong Kong, thereby maintaining the role as an international financial centre. Also, as the administrator of major financial benchmarks (such as HIBOR) in Hong Kong, the TMA uphold the robustness and credibility of the administered benchmarks. This includes reviewing whether and how to refine benchmarks administered having regard to international recommendations and local market conditions. We are currently looking for a candidate to join the benchmark administration team.

Responsible for daily benchmark monitoring/surveillance process and its reporting;
undertake ad-hoc project and testing as required

 Job Requirements

Bachelor’s degree holder (Business degree most preferred) and fresh graduates will also be considered;
Exercising due diligence and attention to detail is crucial;
Good communication, problem-solving and time management skills

Interested parties please send application letters with full resume and expected salary via email to the TMA office.

Data collected will be used for recruitment purposes. Applicants may assume their applications unsuccessful if they are not contacted within one month from the application.

Responsibilities:

Research and structure new product ideas. Familiar with product design procedures, prepare legal documents for fund launching;
Understand the needs of Asset Management market, able to identify product opportunities in the market and matching to targeted customer;
Coordinate with sales team in presenting on-the-shelf products to distribution channels & targeting customers;
Assessing feasibility and profitability of various ad hoc investment proposals;

Requirements:
Minimum 1 years’ experience in finance field, preferable in renowned Asset Management Company;
Experience with offshore fund market will be an advantage;
Able to work independently with good problem solving skill and analytical mindset;
Good team player with excellent communication and interpersonal skills;
Good command of spoken and written Mandarin and English is a MUST.

Job Purpose:
To maintain the stress testing program of the Bank and to perform the risk management functions in relation to capital management matters and interest rate risk in the banking book (IRRBB).
Main Responsibilities:
Maintain and execute the stress testing program and policies including the review of assumptions and methodologies; Play a central role in bank-wide stress testing such as stress tests for ICAAP, recovery planning, capital planning as well as the regulator driven stress testing;
Handle risk-related capital management matters such as ICAAP review, recovery planning, capital triggers;
Measure, monitor and control the IRRBB exposures against approved risk limits and appetite; Maintain proper policies and procedures on IRRBB management;
Maintain and develop risk reports for internal risk monitoring as well as regulatory reporting in accordance with the applicable regulatory standards and requirements;
Perform regular and ad hoc risk analysis, simulations and reporting assigned by the Department Head and senior management including the Asset & Liability Management Committee and other risk committees.
Requirements:
Over 7 years’ experience in the risk management of treasury, asset and liability management or finance related areas in the banking industry;
Hands-on experience in database management or statistical tools, e.g. SQL, SAS, VBA, etc.;
University degree in Finance, Risk Management or equivalent; holder of CFA or FRM an added advantage;
Good knowledge in treasury markets, products, regulatory requirements on risk management and capital adequacy;
Good interpersonal skills and a good team member.
Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.

Job Responsibilities:

Perform FX and Interest Rates Derivates trading, and manage the relevant risks;
Conduct pre/post trades and ad-hoc assignments ;
Consistently perform accurate and timely quote for sales and clients;
Develop trading strategy and make market updates for sales marketing;
Enhance the new product process through interaction with different stakeholders;
Strictly follow trading mandates, including but not restricted to limits, exposure in the individual level and firm level;
Assume ad hoc duties as assigned by the Team Head. 

Job Requirements:

Degree holder in Accounting, Finance, Mathematics, Statistics, Finance or related disciplines
Minimum 5 years working experience in FX and Interest Rates Derivatives, including but not restricted to IRS, CCS, Option on major currencies
Exposure with China onshore rates and rates-related bonds is an advantage
Familiar with dealing systems, such as Reuters, Bloomberg etc
Proficient in professional computer applications, such as VBA, Excel, Word etc
Will have exposure into other products such as onshore rates-related bonds
Strong communication and interpersonal skills, good analytical skill, strong report writing and self-motivated
Ability to work independently
Proficient in both spoken and written English and Chinese; fluent in Putonghua is highly preferable

Candidates with less experience will be considered as Assistant Manager.

